| ‚ùå Remove 5173 & 3000 from public access |         |

From your built file (index-BNUq3tIu.js), Axios is creating an XHR request with an invalid URL

üî• ROOT CAUSE (THIS IS THE REAL ISSUE)
Your frontend build is still using:
‚ùå localhost
‚ùå undefined
‚ùå empty string
‚ùå or a malformed env variable
So Axios ends up doing something like:
xhr.open("GET", "undefined/api/login")
‚û°Ô∏è Browser throws Invalid URL
‚û°Ô∏è Nginx returns 404 because the request never matches /api
‚úÖ THE CORRECT PRODUCTION RULE (IMPORTANT)

In production, when using Nginx reverse proxy, you must:
‚ùó NOT use VITE_API_URL at all
‚ùó NOT use IPs
‚ùó NOT use localhost
You must use relative URLs only.

‚úÖ CORRECT (production-safe)
axios.get("/api/login");
Same for POST:
axios.post("/api/auth/login", data);

‚úÖ This works because:
Browser calls http://98.88.31.96/api/...
Nginx proxies /api ‚Üí localhost:3000

